    <text>
        <body>
            <p>My dear friend:</p>
            <p>
                <del>?</del>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">What shall I say to your complaints and suffering? Am I not<lb/> in
                a much sadder position? I am completely shut <sic>offnfrom</sic> the world. I<lb/>
                cannot hold a literary conversation with anybody. That is what is meant<lb/> by, “He
                who increases knowledge, increases pain”. In addition, I feel<lb/> very poorly.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The proof sheets-the second set — I received only today. I<lb/> have
                corrected them again but only superficially, so that the first are<lb/> probably
                more correct. Nevertheless, I send you these because they are<lb/> corrected more
                neatly.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I did not take the <sic>pentateuch</sic> over. It is too
                expensive.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I send you cordial greetings.</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">Yours sincerely,</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <persName role="author">Jonah Bondi</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="(Other side)"/>
            <p>It is very unpleasant for me not to see printed the entire preface<lb/> and
                introduction. The few lines on II must, in any event, be printed<lb/> over again.
                Please do so. With the Hebrew warning, I am not in<lb/> sympathy. At least in
                    <date>January</date>, more will have to be printed, for<lb/> which I shall send
                you the continuation of the manuscript.</p>
        </body>
    </text>
